<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA PLANS PHYSICAL FITNESS CAMPAIGN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Worried that increased affluence may produce a nation of couch potatoes, the 
Chinese government is planning a campaign to encourage exercise and promote 
fitness. 
</P>
<P>
 The National Sports Commission wants people to take up at least two sports 
each and to exercise at least 20 minutes a day, the China Daily reported 
Monday. 
</P>
