<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: DANA POINT; MEETING TO ADDRESS FUTURE OF LANDFILL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The county is holding a meeting tonight in Dana Point to discuss a draft 
environmental impact report on a plan to guide development of the county's 
Prima Deschecha landfill. 
</P>
<P>
 The 1,530-acre landfill site, in use since 1976, includes unincorporated 
county land and parts of San Juan Capistrano and San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 A new plan for the facility includes a proposal to connect La Pata Avenue at 
the middle of the landfill, near the border of San Juan Capistrano and San 
Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 The landfill is south of Ortega Highway and west of Interstate 5. 
</P>
<P>
 Tonight's meeting is from 7 to 9 at the Youth and Group Facility, 34451 
Ensenada Place, in Dana Point. JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA083094-0040 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 074383 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 30, 1994, Tuesday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 1 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
386 words 
</P>
