<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: COUNTY WEIGHS AIDS EDUCATION GRANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Ventura County Board of Supervisors today will consider two AIDS education 
contracts focusing on Latinas of childbearing age and young gay men. 
</P>
<P>
 El Concilio del Condado de Ventura, a local Latino organization, would be 
awarded $31,900 to provide AIDS education services to the Latino community, 
emphasizing young women, under the proposed contract. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Collins, an AIDS educator at the Gay and Lesbian Resource Center, would 
be awarded $41,000 to provide AIDS prevention services to gay and bisexual men, 
primarily those who are young. 
</P>
<P>
 Both contracts are part of a master funding plan for state-supported AIDS 
education, testing and case management, which was approved by the board last 
week. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan combines four separate programs under one $423,000 grant from the 
state Department of Health Services. MIGUEL BUSTILLO 
</P>
