<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Oxnard woman accused of dropping her infant daughter over a six-foot fence 
pleaded not guilty Monday to battery and child-endangerment charges. 
</P>
<P>
 Aretha Marcell Chester, 23, appeared in Ventura County Superior Court for her 
arraignment and was ordered to stand trial on Sept. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Chester was arrested after an incident on July 31 that witnesses said began 
with an argument between the woman and a group of men at Sierra Linda Park in 
Oxnard. When the men jumped over the chain-link fence, Chester dangled the 
infant over the fence and released her, according to testimony from witnesses 
at a preliminary hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 Chester told police after her arrest that the baby had fallen from a child's 
seat. 
</P>
<P>
 The fall left the baby, Sara Kimbrough, with a fractured skull. The child was 
released from the hospital the next day to the custody of Chester's mother. 
</P>
