<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLOBAL AGRICULTURE; REFLECTIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 " O fortunatos nimium, sua bona norint, Agricolas! " ("O farmers excessively 
fortunate, if only they recognized their blessings!") 
</P>
<P>
 -- Roman poet Virgil (70 B.C.-19 B.C.), from "Georgics," No. 2 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 "Physically, there is nothing to distinguish human society from the farmyard 
