<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN HELD IN WOMAN'S SHOOTING DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police have arrested a man in connection with the fatal shooting of a woman 
Sunday at a house in the 600 block of South Emily Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said the shooting occurred about 3:40 p.m. When paramedics arrived, 
they found the victim lying on the front porch.Witnesses told police they saw a 
man leaving the area with a rifle. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrol officers checking the area found Robert Edroy Thompson, 26, hiding in a 
nearby alley, police said. He was taken into custody and booked on suspicion of 
murder late Sunday night. He was being held on $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Thompson is a nephew of the owner of the house where the victim 
was found. 
</P>
<P>
 Police withheld the victim's identity pending notification of her family. 
</P>
