<P>
KATHLEEN BROWN BRINGS CAMPAIGN TO ORANGE COUNTY FORUM EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 State treasurer and gubernatorial candidate Kathleen Brown will be the 
featured speaker at a public luncheon Wednesday sponsored by the Orange County 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
 The nonprofit, nonpartisan organization provides opportunities for newsmakers 
to discuss issues affecting Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown's campaign rival, Gov. Pete Wilson, has also been invited to address the 
Irvine-based organization prior to the November election. No date has been 
arranged yet for Wilson, according to a forum spokesperson. Recent polls show 
that Brown and Wilson are locked in a tight race. 
</P>
<P>
 A reception for Brown will begin at 11:30 a.m. at the Hyatt Regency Irvine, 
17900 Jamboree Road. The luncheon will follow at noon. Admission is $25 for 
forum members and $35 for non-members. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations: (714) 588-9884. 
</P>
