5-9, 190 -- DL Jr. B.J. Wallace, 6-2, 190 TB DB Jr. OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Century, which comes to the Empire League from the Pacific Coast, is expected 
to contend for third place with Loara and Cypress. Brown says his team will 
rely on a balanced attack, though much of it will depend on Villanueva, who 
threw only six touchdowns last season but suffered 12 interceptions. "He's a 
much more mature quarterback," Brown said. Vega, Armendariz and Rodriguez are 
among the club's top receivers. Wallace and Villegas will give Century a good 
running game, but the Centurions' lack of size, depth and overall team speed 
present problems. "We're not going to blow people away with our speed, but we 
can (compete)," Brown said. "Our receivers can catch the ball and that's our 
biggest threat. Our explosiveness will come from them." SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 September 10 vs. Los Amigos at Santa Ana Stadium; 16 at Norwalk Glenn; 23 vs. 
Ocean View at Huntington Beach HS; 30 vs. Woodbridge at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
