<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; VALLEY COLLEGE GETS $225,000 IN GIFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles Valley College will use $225,000 in donations to fund its writing 
center and replace essential science equipment damaged in the Northridge 
earthquake, school officials announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Alliance for the Advancement of Education donated $200,000 to provide 
additional funding for the Valley College Writing Center Project, the campus 
writing lab. 
</P>
<P>
 The gift will fund the center through June. The group has donated a total of 
$400,000 for the center, which employs student tutors working with computers to 
improve the writing skills of about 250 students each week. 
</P>
<P>
 The donation, the third by the nonprofit group, was made to the college's 
foundation, the Patrons Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The foundation also received $25,000 from Rotary District 5260 to replace four 
telescopes and several life science instruments that were damaged in the Jan. 
17 quake. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
