<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENGLISH OFFER U.S. $25,000 AS INCENTIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 England's Football Assn. on Monday offered the U.S. national soccer team 
$25,000 if it beats England in an exhibition Sept. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 The FA made the unprecedented move because it said it wanted to ensure a 
competitive match at Wembley Stadium as England begins its preparations for the 
1996 European Championships. 
</P>
<P>
 Alexi Lalas, one of the U.S. team's World Cup stars, said a cash incentive is 
not needed. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've beaten England before and we can do it again," said Lalas, now playing 
for the Italian first division club Padova. 
