</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Liberty National Bank: The Huntington Beach bank said it lost $671,137, or 69 
cents a share, for the second quarter.That contrasted with a profit of 
$203,650, or 21 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier. For the 
first half, the company reported a loss of $760,696, or 78 cents a share, 
contrasted with profit of $375,455, or 38 cents a share, for the corresponding 
period last year. Assets as of June 30 declined 13% to $142.7 million from 
$163.1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
