<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: NEW IMAGE REPORTS LOSING $1.61 MILLION IN 4TH QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New Image Industries Inc., the Canoga Park-based developer of dental cameras, 
reported a loss of $1.61 million for its fourth fiscal quarter ended June 30, 
in contrast to earnings of $1.45 million in the same period a year earlier. 
Revenues for the quarter were $8.46 million, up 5% from $8.05 million the year 
before. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year, New Image reported a loss of $347,000, in contrast to 
earnings of $5.61 million in fiscal 1994. The loss was on revenue of $31.6 
million, up 3% from $30.6 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 New Image attributed the fourth-quarter results to its placement of $2 million 
in reserve pending the outcome of a patent infringement lawsuit against the 
company, while it said the annual results were affected by the impact of the 
Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake on its sales operations. 
</P>
