of $12.2 million, compared to a year-earlier loss of $160,000 on revenue of 
$10.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Semtech attributed the results to increased sales volume fueled by the success 
of new products, which accounted for 20% of orders received in the latest 
quarter. 
