<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: BLUE CROSS LAUNCHES PLAN FOR WORKERS' COMP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Blue Cross of California has launched a new managed-care product that will 
provide workers' compensation and medical benefits. 
</P>
<P>
 Called Source One, the new program is available statewide for business groups 
with more than 50 employees, and is offered through CaliforniaCare Health Plans 
and UniCARE Insurance Co., a recently acquired subsidiary of Blue Cross.Blue 
Cross, based in Woodland Hills, is the majority shareholder of WellPoint Health 
Networks Inc., the holding company for CaliforniaCare Health Plans. 
</P>
<P>
 The new program applies the cost-saving strategies associated with health 
maintenance organizations to workers' compensation. Blue Cross said Source One 
could save employers money through negotiated agreements with experts in 
specialties most often used for the treatment of severe worker injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 Blue Cross said the program also saves money by monitoring patients' treatment 
and consolidating administrative tasks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
